<subSubSection id="9CE65A8DFFC7FFFDFCFB67E6FAEFFC50" pageId="14" pageNumber="1086" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="D4430906FFC7FFFDFCFB67E6FB5BFD57" blockId="14.[827,1443,487,724]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1086">
<emphasis id="E688D514FFC7FFFDFCFB67E6FC4DFE79" box="[827,952,488,509]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1086">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Body posteriorly extended into a short peristomial projection and slightly constricted at level of macronucleus; macronucleus oriented with its longer axis perpendicularly to main body axis; karyophore present, attached to right and left body margins; adoral zone of membranelles on left and paroral membrane on right side of vestibulum. Diagnostic molecular characters as shown in 
<figureCitation id="4CC71583FFC7FFFDFB8764B0FB52FD57" box="[1095,1191,702,724]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="20.[163,242,1698,1720]" captionTargetBox="[166,1441,197,1657]" captionTargetId="figure-30@20.[163,1443,195,1658]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figure 8. Diagram of the morpho-molecular evolution of the family Clevelandellidae based on the present phylogenetic analyses. Molecular diagnostic characters are displayed for each marker in two rows: the upper row refers to the group in question (i.e. query group) and the lower row to the reference group, which includes all remaining clevelandellids and nyctotherids. Numbers correspond to the position of characters in the reference alignments. AZM, adoral zone of membranelles; MA, macronucleus; PM, paroral membrane." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6459106" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6459106/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="1086">Figure 8</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D4430906FFC7FFFDFCFB650BFA90FCBC" blockId="14.[827,1443,772,825]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1086">
<emphasis id="E688D514FFC7FFFDFCFB650BFC3BFC9E" box="[827,974,773,794]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1086">
<typeStatus id="0B47B7A4FFC7FFFDFCFB650BFC84FC9E" box="[827,881,773,794]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1086">Type</typeStatus>
species:
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="13FC7285FFC7FFFDFC22650AFA75FC9D" authority="Kidder, 1937" authorityName="Kidder" authorityYear="1937" box="[994,1408,772,794]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Orobanchaceae" genus="Clevelandia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="1086" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="constricta">
<emphasis id="E688D514FFC7FFFDFC22650AFB10FC9E" box="[994,1253,772,794]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1086">Clevelandia constricta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="B06D74F7FFC7FFFDFB2D650AFA75FC9D" author="Kidder GW" box="[1261,1408,772,794]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1086" pagination="163 - 205" refId="ref17911" refString="Kidder GW. 1937. The intestinal protozoa of the wood-feeding roach Panesthia. Parasitology 29: 163 - 205." type="journal article" year="1937">Kidder, 1937</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by original designation (Article 68.2 of 
<bibRefCitation id="B06D74F7FFC7FFFDFB14652DFAA0FCBC" author="ICZN" box="[1236,1365,803,824]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1086" refId="ref17784" refString="ICZN. 1999. International Code of Zoological Nomenclature, 4 th edn. London: International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature." type="book" year="1999">ICZN, 1999</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D4430906FFC7FFFDFCFB656CFAEFFC50" blockId="14.[827,1447,866,980]" pageId="14" pageNumber="1086">
<emphasis id="E688D514FFC7FFFDFCFB656CFC37FCF3" box="[827,962,866,887]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1086">Etymology:</emphasis>
Composed of the Latin adverb 
<emphasis id="E688D514FFC7FFFDFAA0656CFA52FCF3" box="[1376,1447,866,887]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1086">anteā</emphasis>
(before, earlier) and the generic name 
<taxonomicName id="13FC7285FFC7FFFDFB3E658EFA68FC11" box="[1278,1437,896,917]" class="Heterotrichea" family="Clevelandellidae" genus="Clevelandella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Heterotrichida" pageId="14" pageNumber="1086" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E688D514FFC7FFFDFB3E658EFA68FC11" box="[1278,1437,896,917]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="1086">Clevelandella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, reflecting the deep branching of this genus within the family 
<taxonomicName id="13FC7285FFC7FFFDFC4A65B0FBBFFC50" authorityName="Kidder" authorityYear="1938" box="[906,1098,958,980]" class="Heterotrichea" family="Clevelandellidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Heterotrichida" pageId="14" pageNumber="1086" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="family">Clevelandellidae</taxonomicName>
. Feminine gender.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
